</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR142:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR142"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              142-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 142</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 134</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Deputies Floyd and Michael Coleman Memorial Highway. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 26, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 142, Ransom.
                          San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Deputies Floyd and Michael Coleman Memorial Highway.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate a specified portion of State Route 120 in the County of San Joaquin as the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Deputies Floyd and Michael Coleman Memorial Highway. The measure would request that the Department of Transportation determine the cost of appropriate signs showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_3BF3EA76-0D5A-49F6-94B4-4E0ACE254F56"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Floyd Coleman and his son, Michael Coleman, lived in the City of Manteca; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_824A56DB-946B-4DEE-B663-05A956AF5BD0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Michael Coleman attended schools in the City of Manteca; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E9938769-CBF8-4ECB-9DE4-D76816E8E601"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Floyd Coleman was sworn in as a member of the sheriff’s auxiliary in 1954; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_267E4974-9E17-429C-9A8D-ADB26020C1A7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Michael Coleman joined the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Office as a cadet and he was promoted one year later to a deputy, with his father pinning his gold star on Michael’s chest; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_14B4A4EF-FA19-446D-81EB-525B21A0C9CF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Floyd Coleman served as the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Office’s Rangemaster, teaching young deputies the techniques necessary to properly use a firearm; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_EDA808C5-B2A4-4DF8-98F1-0BBD2FBA4A6A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Michael worked in the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Office’s Custody Division and Patrol Division, and he worked as an undercover detective in the Metropolitan Narcotics Task Force; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F204394B-8D48-411E-9043-B691CDFA2BEB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On March 25, 1982, Floyd Coleman was working at the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Office’s range, and the Metropolitan Narcotics Task Force was assigned to serve a search warrant for drugs in the City of Stockton; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FB6B3E62-7240-47D3-8451-1A22CD1B4508"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Detective Michael Coleman responded and an exchange of gunfire occurred during the service of the search warrant, resulting in Detective Michael Coleman being shot; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_4E2BFBFC-D751-4251-AFC6-A2A6EA67895C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Detective Michael Coleman was transported to Dameron Hospital in the City of Stockton; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_73810F55-A791-4E0B-A39B-24D50C6D321E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A patrol unit responded to the range to transport Floyd Coleman to the hospital, and as they approached the hospital, Floyd slumped forward; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_33A1F867-1A3B-4936-ABEF-5C97776AC568"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Floyd had suffered a heart attack, and he was rushed into an examination room inside the hospital, but it was too late; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_DD8FF0EB-D617-4E54-9E70-CDA66BB77312"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Floyd and Michael Coleman were pronounced dead, and were later laid to rest side by side; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6CC27D1B-6358-4CFA-AE82-42FFE6809278"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Floyd and Michael Coleman are both buried in St. John’s Catholic Cemetery in the City of Escalon; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_26A88607-CEE4-40D9-B545-217036161EA7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Floyd and Michael Coleman will be remembered for their hard work and dedication to professionalism in law enforcement, and they will be profoundly missed by all; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_980E78E6-B2A2-4E40-9005-B2A83AD2D189"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the portion of State Route 120 from S Van Allen Road, at postmile 13.83, to N Ripon Road, at postmile 9.82, in the County of San Joaquin as the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Deputies Floyd and Michael Coleman Memorial Highway; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_4979E3FD-9702-4C65-98EE-637326A89BFD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Department of Transportation is requested to determine the cost of appropriate signs, consistent with the signing requirements for the state highway system, showing this special designation and, upon receiving donations from nonstate sources sufficient to cover the cost, to erect those signs; and be it further </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_5AE9D35A-DD57-4852-8C6A-BB475E43AE55"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the Director of Transportation and the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
